OL,3,CWes Streeting resigns, paving way for
OL,4,Cleadership coup against Starmer
OL,6,FReferencing the disastrous defeat at
OL,7,Flast week's election, Streeting said:
OL,8,F"It is now clear that you will not
OL,9,Flead the Labour Party into the next
OL,10,Fgeneral election and that Labour MPs
OL,11,Fand Labour Unions want the debate
OL,12,Fabout what comes next to be a battle
OL,13,Fof ideas, not of personalities or
OL,14,Fpetty factionalism.
OL,16,F"It needs to be broad, and it needs
OL,17,Fthe best possible field of candidates.
OL,18,FI support that approach, and I hope
OL,19,Fthat you will facilitate this."
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/14
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
