PN,30406
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F304A1778825170
OL,3,CWes Streeting resigns, paving way for
OL,4,Cleadership coup against Starmer
OL,6,FLabour slumped to third place in
OL,7,FWales, suffered its worst ever result
OL,8,Fin Scotland, and lost hundreds of
OL,9,FEnglish Council seats to Reform UK.
OL,11,FIn his resignation letter, Streting
OL,12,Fwrote: "Last week's election results
OL,13,Fwere unprecedented ` both in terms of
OL,14,Fthe scale of the defeat and the
OL,15,Fconsequences of that failure."
OL,17,FStarmer had attempted to reset his
OL,18,Fgovernment on Monday with a speech
OL,19,Fwhere he promised sweeping reforms and
OL,20,Fplans to unify the nation.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/14
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,305,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30407
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F304A1778825170
OL,3,CWes Streeting resigns, paving way for
OL,4,Cleadership coup against Starmer
OL,6,FInstead, he was met with four
OL,7,Fministerial resignations and as many
OL,8,Fas 93 MPs either calling for him to go
OL,9,Fwith immediate effect, or set out a
OL,10,Ftimeline for his future departure.
OL,11,FEither way, 22% of his own party want
OL,12,Fhim gone.
OL,14,FStreeting's resignation does not
OL,15,Fimmediately trigger a leadership
OL,16,Fcontest, with any MP wishing to do so
OL,17,Fneeding the public backing of 81
OL,18,FLabour MPs to do so.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/14
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
